Hello! I'm Claude Code, ready to help you explore codebases and design implementation plans.

I can see we're in a git repository at `/home/ubuntu`. Let me check what we're working with:

<function_calls>
<invoke name="bash">
<parameter name="command">cd /home/ubuntu && ls -la</parameter>
</invoke>
</function_calls>
<function_calls>
<invoke name="bash">
<parameter name="command">cd /home/ubuntu && find . -type f -name "*.json" -o -name "*.md" -o -name "*.txt" | head -20</parameter>
</invoke>
</function_calls>
<function_calls>
<invoke name="bash">
<parameter name="command">cd /home/ubuntu && git log --oneline -10</parameter>
</invoke>
</function_calls>

I'm warmed up and ready to work! I'm operating in **READ-ONLY mode** - I can explore your codebase, understand its structure, and design implementation plans, but I won't create or modify any files.

What would you like me to help you design or plan today?
